import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of deaths caused by disasters over time?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='Entity', y='Deaths', data=data, ci=None)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths caused by different types of disasters?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='ignore')
    mean_deaths = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Entity', y='Deaths', data=mean_deaths)
    plt.title('What is the average number of deaths caused by each type of disaster?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='ignore')
    deaths_by_entity = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum()
    plt.pie(deaths_by_entity, labels=deaths_by_entity.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the total number of deaths caused by each type of disaster?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
